plexities of embodying the position of researcher and what it was like to do research with these participants. We, as readers, are compelled not only to see how these young people express knowledge about their worlds and their understandings of race, gender, sexuality, class, and age but also to appraise how we make sense of them in the course of our reading.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aEducation : Educational Research. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aEDUCATION / Research.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2024z978311149259940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849707540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438497075423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438497075/original  a978-3-11-149259-9  SUNY Press eBook Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles